  "response": "In Hinduism, there isn't a direct equivalent to \"Rest in Peace\" (RIP) that is universally used. However, there are several phrases and concepts related to death and afterlife in Hinduism:\n\n1. \"Om Shanti\" - This is a common phrase meaning \"Peace\" and is often used during funerals and memorial services.\n\n2. \"Moksha\" - This refers to the ultimate spiritual goal of liberation from the cycle of rebirth (samsara), which is considered the final peaceful state of the soul.\n\nWhile these don't function exactly like \"Rest in Peace,\" they are close spiritual expressions associated with death and peace in the Hindu tradition.",
